What is android?

-Operating system and programming platform developed by Google for smartphones and other mobile devices(such as tablets).
-it can run on many different devices from many different manufactures.
-It includes a software development kit(SDK) for writing original code and assembling software modules to create apps for Android users.

Architecture of Android

1. Sytem Apps && User Apps
2. Java Api Framework
3. Native C/C++ Libraries && Android Runtime
4. Hardware Abstraction Layer(HAL)  
5. Linux Kernel
6. Power Management

1. System Apps
Dialer, Email, Calendar, Camera,...

2. Java Api Framework
i.Content Providers
ii.View System
iii.Managers
a. Activity
b. Location
c. Package
d. Notification
e. Resource
f. Telephony
g. Window

3. Native C/C++ Libraries
a. Webkit
b. OpenMAX AL
c. Libc
d. Media Framework
e. OpenGL ES
Android Runtime
a.Android Runtime(ART)
b.Core Libraries

4. Hardware Abstraction Layer(HAL)
a. Audio
b. Bluetooth
c. Camera 
d. Sensors

5. Linux Kernel
a. Audio
b. Binder(IPC)
c. Display
d. Keypad
e. Bluetooth
f. Camera
g. Shared Memory 
h. USB
i. WIFI

6. Power Management
